; one sine, main knob picks the pitch across two octaves starting at C3.
;   knob-main = pitch (C3 to B4)     audio-out-1 = sine
;
; (spread knob-main 24) divides the knob into 24 semitone buckets. Each bucket
; is about 170 ADC units wide, comfortably outside the framework's knob jitter,
; so the pitch sits stably on each semitone. C3 env-resolves to MIDI 48;
; the positional pitch on sine is in MIDI domain (no auto-spread).
(patch
  (<- (audio-out :1) (sine (add C3 (spread (knob :main) 24)))))
